"title": "4544: wine",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4544: wine",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Drink made from fermented grape juice, often drunk instead of water in biblical times. Scripture recognises the richness of wine and its value in bringing joy to people; however, it condemns the excessive drinking of wine, and recommends total abstinence in some situations.</p>\n<h2>Offerings of wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:5\">NUM 15:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:40\">EXO 29:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:12-Lev23:13\">LEV 23:12–23:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:14\">NUM 28:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:37-Deut32:38\">DEU 32:37–32:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:24\">1SA 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:8-Ezra6:10\">EZR 6:8–6:10</a></p>\n<h2>Tithes and firstfruits of wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:12\">NEH 13:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:11-Num18:12\">NUM 18:11–18:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:17\">DEU 12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:23-Deut14:26\">DEU 14:23–14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:4-Deut18:5\">DEU 18:4–18:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:4-2Chr31:5\">2CH 31:4–31:5</a></p>\n<h2>Wine as a sign of blessing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:28\">GEN 27:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:13\">DEU 7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:13-Deut11:14\">DEU 11:13–11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:28\">DEU 33:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:31-2Kgs18:32\">2KI 18:31–18:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:40\">1CH 12:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:7\">PSA 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:9-Prov3:10\">PRO 3:9–3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:12\">JER 31:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:18-Joel2:24\">JOL 2:18–2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:18\">JOL 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:13-Amos9:14\">AMO 9:13–9:14</a></p>\n<h2>Lack of wine as a sign of God's displeasure</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:33\">JER 48:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:38-Deut28:51\">DEU 28:38–28:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:7-Isa24:9\">ISA 24:7–24:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:10\">JOL 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:14-Hag2:16\">HAG 2:14–2:16</a></p>\n<h2>Wine as an alternative to water</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:23\">1TI 5:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:17-Gen14:18\">GEN 14:17–14:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:19\">JDG 19:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:12\">LAM 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:48\">MAT 27:48</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:36\">MRK 15:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:36\">LUK 23:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:28-John19:29\">JHN 19:28–19:29</a></p>\n<h2>Wine with meals</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:25\">GEN 27:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:14\">RUT 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:18-Job1:19\">JOB 1:18–1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:1-Prov9:6\">PRO 9:1–9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:13\">ISA 22:13</a></p>\n<h2>The pleasant taste and effects of wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:6\">ISA 25:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:12-Judg9:13\">JDG 9:12–9:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:14-Ps104:15\">PSA 104:14–104:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:7\">ECC 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:19\">ECC 10:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:2-Song1:4\">SNG 1:2–1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:10\">SNG 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:8-Song7:9\">SNG 7:8–7:9</a></p>\n<h2>The dangers of drinking wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:1\">PRO 20:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:20-Gen9:27\">GEN 9:20–9:27</a> <em>Noah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:30-Gen19:38\">GEN 19:30–19:38</a> <em>Lot and his daughters</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:13-1Sam1:15\">1SA 1:13–1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:28\">2SA 13:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:10-Esth1:12\">EST 1:10–1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:1\">ISA 28:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:7\">ISA 28:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:3-Hos7:5\">HOS 7:3–7:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:5\">JOL 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:9-Nah1:10\">NAM 1:9–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:1-Acts2:21\">ACT 2:1–2:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:18\">EPH 5:18</a></p>\n<h2>The irresponsibility of wine drinkers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:17\">PRO 21:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:19-Prov23:21\">PRO 23:19–23:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:29-Prov23:35\">PRO 23:29–23:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:4-Prov31:7\">PRO 31:4–31:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:3\">ECC 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:11-Isa5:12\">ISA 5:11–5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:22-Isa5:23\">ISA 5:22–5:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:13\">ISA 22:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:12\">ISA 56:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:11\">MIC 2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Abstinence from wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:9\">LEV 10:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:1-Num6:21\">NUM 6:1–6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:2-Judg13:7\">JDG 13:2–13:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:1-Jer35:19\">JER 35:1–35:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:21\">EZK 44:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:3-Dan1:16\">DAN 1:3–1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:1-Dan10:3\">DAN 10:1–10:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:11-Amos2:12\">AMO 2:11–2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:11-Luke1:17\">LUK 1:11–1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:33\">LUK 7:33</a></p>\n<h2>Stores of wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:28\">2CH 32:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:29\">1CH 9:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:27\">1CH 27:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:11-2Chr11:12\">2CH 11:11–11:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:37-Neh10:39\">NEH 10:37–10:39</a></p>\n<h2>Wine stewards</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:7-Esth1:8\">EST 1:7–1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:1-Gen40:13\">GEN 40:1–40:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:11-Neh2:1\">NEH 1:11–2:1</a></p>\n<h2>Trade in wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:3\">JOL 3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:11-Rev18:13\">REV 18:11–18:13</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's miracle of water turned into wine</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:1-John2:11\">JHN 2:1–2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Drugged wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:34\">MAT 27:34</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:23\">MRK 15:23</a></p>\n<h2>Metaphorical use of wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps75:8\">PSA 75:8</a></strong> <em>God's wrath is often pictured as a cup of wine to be drunk.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:11-Gen49:12\">GEN 49:11–49:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:19\">JOB 32:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps60:3\">PSA 60:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:65\">PSA 78:65</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:17\">PRO 4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:1\">ISA 55:1</a> <em>quenching spiritual thirst</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:9\">JER 23:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:15\">JER 25:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:11\">JER 48:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:7\">JER 51:7</a> <em>illustrating judgment and the moral decadence of Babylon the Great</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:8-Rev14:10\">REV 14:8–14:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:19\">REV 16:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:1-Rev17:2\">REV 17:1–17:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:3\">REV 18:3</a></p>\n<h2>Wine as a symbol of the suffering and death of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:20\">LUK 22:20</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:27-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:27–26:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:23-Mark14:24\">MRK 14:23–14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:25-1Cor11:26\">1CO 11:25–11:26</a></p>",
